<title>USA: Specialty Chemical buys aerosol producer.</title>
<headline>Specialty Chemical buys aerosol producer.</headline>
<dateline>MACEDONIA, Ohio 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Specialty Chemical Resources Inc said it has acquired the assets of Hysan Corp, a producer of aerosols and liquid specialty chemical maintenance products for an undisclosed amount of cash.</p>
<p>Hysan is a subsidiary of Wedge Energy Group Inc of Houston.</p>
<p>Specialty Chemical Chairman and Chief Executive Edwin Roth said in a statement that the assets being acquired include the Hysan trade name, its proprietary formulas, inventory, receivables, and equipment.</p>
<p>Manufacturing operations are to be moved from Illinois to Specialty Chemicals' facilities in Macedonia, Ohio, early this summer, the company said.</p>
<p>The company said it will add about 25 people to accommodate increased production levels on its aerosol lines.</p>
<p>((-- New York Newsdesk 212-859-1610))</p>
